#DESCRIPTION
Hybrid PIC (kinetic ions / fluid electrons) parallel whistler-Alfven wave test.
Validates the generalized Ohm's law with the Hall term in normalized CGS units.

Parameters are chosen so that in CODE (normalized) units the ion scales are
O(1) and the ion cyclotron motion is resolved by the timestep:
  The geometry is in code units; the box is Lx = 6.4 d_i.
  Normalization: lNormSI = ion inertial length d_i, uNormSI = Alfven speed v_A,
  so that d_i ~ 1, v_A ~ 1, and (with q/(m c)=1 for the proton) B = Omega_i ~ 1.
  With dt = 0.02, dt*Omega_i = 0.02 << 1, so the Hall/whistler mode
  (bounded by Omega_i, since omega/Omega_i = (k d_i)^2 / (1+(k d_i)^2)) is
  numerically stable.  Physical inputs (n = 5 amu/cc, B = 5.22 nT,
  v_A ~ 51 km/s, d_i ~ 102 km) are solar-wind-like.

#INITFROMSWMF
F                       initFromSWMF

#GEOMETRY
-3.2                    xMin  [code units; Lx = 6.4 d_i]
 3.2                    xMax
-0.05                   yMin
 0.05                   yMax
-0.05                   zMin
 0.05                   zMax

#NCELL
64                      nCellX
1                       nCellY
1                       nCellZ

#MAXBLOCKSIZE
64                      maxBlockSizeX
1                       maxBlockSizeY
1                       maxBlockSizeZ

#PERIODICITY
T                       isPeriodicX
T                       isPeriodicY
T                       isPeriodicZ

#SOLVEEM
F                       solveEM

#HYBRIDPIC
T                       useHybridPIC

#RESISTIVITY
0.0                     etaResistivity

#ELECTRONTEMPERATURE
0.0                     electronTemperature
1.0                     electronGamma
1.0                     electronDensity0

#HALLSUBCYCLE
32                      nHallSubcycle   subDt=dt/32=6.25e-4 satisfies Hall CFL dx^2/(6 v_A d_i)

#PLASMA
1                       nSpecies
1.0                     mass        Species 0: kinetic ion (electron is implicit fluid)
1.0                     charge

#UNIFORMSTATE
5.0                     rho [amu/cc]   Species 0: ions (n = 5 /cc)
0.0                     ux [km/s]
0.0                     uy [km/s]
0.0                     uz [km/s]
10000.0                 T [K]
5.2195e-9               bx [T]       uniform guide field Bx0 (B_code ~ 1)
0.0                     by [T]
0.0                     bz [T]
0.0                     ex [V/m]
0.0                     ey [V/m]
0.0                     ez [V/m]

#TESTCASE
HybridWave

#TIMESTEPPING
T                       useFixedDt
0.02                    dt

#NORMALIZATION
1.0e5                   lNormSI   [m]  ~ d_i so d_i ~ 1 in code units
5.0e4                   uNormSI   [m/s] ~ v_A so v_A ~ 1 in code units

#MONITOR
1                       dnReport

#SAVELOG
1                       dnSavePic
1                       dnSavePT

#PARTICLES
2000                    nParticle per cell in X
1                       nParticle per cell in Y
1                       nParticle per cell in Z

#COMOVING
F                       solvePartInCoMov
0                       nSmoothBackGroundU

#UPWINDE
F                       useUpwindE
0.0                     limiterThetaE

#UPWINDB
F                       doSmoothB
0.0                     theta

#SAVEPLOT
1                       nPlot
z=0 fluid ascii pic     plotString
-1                      dn
0.5                     dt
1                       dx
Bx By Bz Ex Ey Ez       varName

#STOP
-1                      MaxIter
6.25                    TimeMax

#RUN
